# System Rules and Context

## 1. Primary Design Guide

Always reference the **[Style Guide](docs/style-guide.md)** before writing new React components, applying CSS, or adding new pages. It contains strict rules regarding:

- Typography (`ABC Camera Plain` and `Flecha S`)
- Core design tokens (colors, backgrounds, text colors)
- Custom Headless UI components (`Button`, `Section`, `Container`)

## 2. Dependencies & Stack

- We use **Next.js 16** (App Router).
- We use **Tailwind CSS v4** (`@theme` in `globals.css`).
- We use **@headlessui/react** for unstyled accessible primitives.
- **NEVER** use Shadcn, Radix UI, Class Variance Authority (CVA), or Tailwind Merge. They were explicitly removed.
- **NEVER** use hardcoded hex codes for colors or explicit font names in inline classes (e.g., `text-[#FF0000]` or `font-['Arial']`). Use the defined Tailwind theme variables (`bg-background`, `text-muted`, `bg-surface`, `text-accent`, etc.).

## 3. Architecture & File Structure

- Page-specific components go in their respective `app/[page]/components/` folders (e.g., `app/about/components/TeamSection.tsx`).
- Shared UI primitives go in `app/components/ui/` (e.g., `Button.tsx`, `Container.tsx`, `Section.tsx`).
- Global layout components (Header, Footer) go in `app/components/[Name]/`.
- Font configurations are centralized in `app/theme/fonts.ts`.
- CSS variables are centralized in `app/globals.css`.

## 4. Fonts and Weights

The project relies on a variable font for sans-serif text (`ABCCameraPlainVariable.woff2`).

- To adjust the weight of `font-sans`, simply use standard Tailwind font-weight classes: `font-light`, `font-normal`, `font-medium`, `font-semibold`, `font-bold`. The variable font handles the rendering automatically.
- The serif font (`FlechaS`) is static and supports `font-light` and `font-normal` weights. It is reserved exclusively for large headings (`font-serif`).

## 5. Assets

- Use local SVG placeholders located in `public/images/` instead of remote URLs like `placehold.co`. This prevents `next/image` domain configuration issues and timeouts during static generation.

